2026-06-22 | Container With Most Water

Question
Return the maximum rectangular area that can be formed.
	Key Insight
A brute-force solution checks every pair:
		O(n²)
This is too slow.
Use Two Pointers:
		left = 0
		right = n-1
At every step:
		area =
		min(height[left], height[right])
		×
		(right-left)
Update answer.
Then move the shorter bar:
•	If left bar is smaller,
		move left forward.
•	If right bar is smaller,
		move right backward.
Why?
The area is limited by the shorter bar. Keeping it and reducing width can never improve the answer. We must try to find a taller bar.
	Approach
1.	Initialize:
			left = 0
			right = n-1
2.	While left < right:
			compute area
			update answer
3.	Move the pointer at the smaller height.
4.	Continue until pointers meet.
5.	Return answer.
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int maxArea(vector<int>& height) {
        int left = 0;
        int right = height.size() - 1;
        long long ans = 0;
        while(left < right) {
            long long area =
                1LL * min(height[left],
                          height[right])
                * (right - left);
            ans = max(ans, area);
            if(height[left] < height[right])
                left++;
            else
                right--;
        }
        return (int)ans;
    }
};
	Example
	Input:
			[1,8,6,2,5,4,8,3,7]
	Best choice:
			height 8 at index 1
			height 7 at index 8
	Area:
			min(8,7) × (8-1)
			= 7 × 7
			= 49
	Output:
			49
	Key Insight
The width decreases whenever we move a pointer. Therefore, the only way to potentially increase the area is to look for a taller bar than the current shorter one. This observation leads to the optimal O(n) two-pointer solution.
